## AUTO-DETECT (no keyword)

  existing repo + any task               → Explore: first, then task trigger
  understand / what patterns / how is X  → Explore:
  is this in sync / does this match      → Sync:
  LLD / low level design / class diagram → LLD:
  HLD / system design / architecture doc → HLD:
  microservice / service boundary / DDD  → Micro:
  break up monolith / extract service    → Decompose:
  new service / service scaffold         → Scaffold:
  service contract / inter-service API   → Contract:
  distributed tracing / OTel / SLO       → Trace:
  ADR / architecture decision / why did  → ADR:
  build/create/make + app/feature        → Workflow:
  fix/bug/error/broken                   → Bug:
  write tests / unit test / coverage     → Test:
  docker/deploy/CI-CD/pipeline           → DevOps:
  git/branch/commit/PR                   → Git:
  MCP server / expose to AI              → MCP:
  release/hotfix/changelog               → Release:
  AWS/S3/EC2/Lambda/Terraform            → Infra:
  write docs / runbook / ADR             → Doc:
  monitoring/alerting/tracing            → Observe:
  incident/outage/post-mortem            → Incident:
  data pipeline/ETL/warehouse            → Data:
  research/compare/evaluate              → Research:
  prompt/system prompt                   → Prompt:
  LLM/AI feature/Claude                  → AI:
  RAG/fine-tune/ML pipeline              → ML:
  API design/OpenAPI                     → API:
  monorepo/turborepo                     → Monorepo:
  review/audit code                      → Review:
